nib.text:
One woman was killed and 14 people were injured in a shooting at a bar in Irvine Park early Sunday morning, police said. 

At 12:15 a.m., police responded to multiple reports of a shooting in or near the Seventh Street Truck Park bar on the 200 block of West Seventh Street. 

SPPD officials said responding officers arrived to a "chaotic scene" where they located 15 gunshot wound victims. 

Officers secured the scene and began rendering aid to the victims with help from good Samaritans, according to officials.

Medics pronounced a woman believed to be in her 20s dead at the scene.

The other 14 victims were transported to area hospitals, where they are all expected to survive their injuries.

During a preliminary investigation, police learned there were likely several shooters, but it is unclear what led to the gunfire and if the victims were bystanders or intended targets. 

No suspects are in custody. 

An investigation is ongoing.

Anyone with information about the incident is asked to call investigators at 651-266-5650.
